<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8d03201-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s541"><num value="541">§ 541.</num><heading> Entry of goods falsely classified</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever knowingly effects any entry of goods, wares, or merchandise, at less than the true weight or measure thereof, or upon a false classification as to quality or value, or by the payment of less than the amount of duty legally due, shall be fined under this title or imprisoned not more than two years, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb8d03202-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/715">62 Stat. 715</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXXXIII/s330016/1/K">Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXIII, § 330016(1)(K)</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2147">108 Stat. 2147</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb8d03203-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idb8d03204-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 126 (<ref href="/us/act/1909-03-04/ch321/s69">Mar. 4, 1909, ch. 321, § 69</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/35/1101">35 Stat. 1101</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Reference to persons aiding, contained in words “or aid in effecting,” was omitted as unnecessary as such persons are made principals by <ref href="/us/usc/t18/s2">section 2 of this title</ref>.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb8d03205-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb8d03206-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—<ref href="/us/pl/103/322">Pub. L. 103–322</ref> substituted “fined under this title” for “fined not more than $5,000”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
